{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 256.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "For breakfast, we usually got a little bit of milk and that's all you got.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "No seconds.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And if something happened to that, that's it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I remember one day, I accidentally spilled the milk and there was just a little bit left in the cup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I remembered how cats drank their milk and I put my tongue to that and that little bit that remained in the cup and made that do.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I just-- touching the tip of my tongue to that milk.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And it actually filled me up to-- to be able to do that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I was proud of myself that I could-- that I had the discipline to learn how to deal with adversity.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But anyways, back-- now going back to Seyre et Nailloux, we lived there for about a year.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And during that time, conditions got more severe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "The Germans started making more demands, the-- the French police started reporting that the-- the Jews were not welcome.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then all of a sudden, the-- the announcement came, any Jew 16 years old and older had to report to the police station.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we all knew what that meant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I mean, it meant you're going to be deported, probably sent to some camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So of course, arrangements were made immediately to try and go into hiding.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And the older ones left and went south into the Pyrenees near Foix, F-O-I-X, looking for a place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And they found an old abandoned castle, 15th-16th century castle, that was called Castle of the hill.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The French were is Chateau de la Hille.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Chateau de la Hille is spelled Chateau and hille is spelled H-I-L-L-E.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
